{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πόντ-ιος</b>, α, ον, <br /> also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 595 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (πόντος):— <b>of the sea,</b> epithet of Poseidon, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hymni Homerici” 22.3, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1072 (Lyric poetry), etc.; πόντιε 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 1010 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. Θέτις, Νηρηΐδες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.35, p. 11.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. δάκη <b>sea</b> monsters, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 582 (Lyric poetry); π. βόσκημα [prev. author] “fragment” 275 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; π. ὕδωρ, πέλαγος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 2.64, 7.56 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κύματα, θύελλα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 89, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1659, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ᾅδην π. πεφευγότες, i.e. death by drowning, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 667. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> π. ῥάκη, of sponges or fragments of such, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Tragica Adespota” 258. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>by the sea,</b> of places, Ἰσθμός, ἀκτή, Χρύση, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.48, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 449, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 269. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>in the sea,</b> of islands, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially of those <b>far out to sea,</b> opposed to πρόσγειοι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 368b33, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.6.2, 8.6.6 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of ships, βάριδες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 553 (Lyric poetry); ὅπλισμα 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 253 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> of persons, ἱκέτας δέχεσθαι ποντίους <b>from the sea,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyc.” 300 \">Refs</a>]; ἀφιέναι πόντιον <b>into the sea,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Hec.” 797. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> <b>brought by sea</b> or <b>from beyond sea,</b> of iron, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 940 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4194","accentedUnicode":"Πόντιος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4091","matchingForm":"Πιλᾶτος","stepTransliteration":"pilatos","gloss":"Pilate","_searchResultRange":"Matt.27.2-1Tim.6.13","_zh_tw_Gloss":"彼拉多","_es_Gloss":"Pilato","_zh_Gloss":"彼拉多"},{"strongNumber":"G4194","matchingForm":"Πόντιος","stepTransliteration":"pontios","gloss":"Pontius","_searchResultRange":"Luke.3.1-1Tim.6.13@Matt.27.2-1Tim.6.13","_zh_tw_Gloss":"本丟","_es_Gloss":"Poncio","_zh_Gloss":"本丢"}],"shortDef":"Pontius, \"[tribal name]\"","mediumDef":"A man living at the time of the New Testament, first mentioned at Mat.27.2; also called Pontius at Mat.27.2; 3x <BR> § Pontius, \"[tribal name]\" <br /><b>Pontius,</b> (Proper name), <ref='Act.4.27'>Acts 4:27</ref>","stepGloss":"Pontius","stepTransliteration":"pontios","count":4,"_es_Definition":"Poncio","_zh_tw_Definition":"本丟[彼拉多] 这个陽性專有名詞在拉丁文的意思是 \"屬於海的\"<br>將耶穌釘死十字架的第六任羅馬派駐猶大行政官","_zh_Definition":"本丢[彼拉多] 这个阳性专有名词在拉丁文的意思是 \"属于海的\"<br>将耶稣钉死十字架的第六任罗马派驻犹大行政官","_step_Type":"man","_step_Link":"Pilate@Mat.27.2-1Ti","_stepDetailLexicalTag":"[[\"